        print(f"{word}\t1")

# 🧾 🔹 STEP 8: Create Reducer
nano reducer.py
Paste:
#!/usr/bin/env python3
import sys

current_word = None
current_count = 0

for line in sys.stdin:
    word, count = line.strip().split("\t")
    count = int(count)

    if current_word == word:
        current_count += count
    else:
        if current_word:
            print(f"{current_word}\t{current_count}")
        current_word = word
        current_count = count

if current_word:
    print(f"{current_word}\t{current_count}")
```
STEP 9: Give Permissions
chmod +x mapper.py reducer.py

STEP 10: Put File in HDFS

bash
hdfs dfs -mkdir /input
hdfs dfs -put input.txt /input

STEP 11: Run MapReduce
hadoop jar $HADOOP_HOME/share/hadoop/tools/lib/hadoop-streaming*.jar \
-input /input/input.txt \
-output /output \
-mapper mapper.py \
-reducer reducer.py

STEP 12: View Output
hdfs dfs -cat /output/part-00000

Expected:
ai      1
hello   3
neha    1
world   2
STEP 13: Run Again (IMPORTANT)

Before running again:

hdfs dfs -rm -r /output

